# 969c04d613eb4e3d8d8ee0ed77c55675
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:23
msgid "HTTP Alternate Selection"
msgstr ""

# 827a1fddedf44ff68625ab1b0e8d2ecc
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:25
msgid ""
"The HTTP alternate selection functions provide a mechanism for hooking "
"into Traffic Server's alternate selection mechanism and augmenting it "
"with additional information. **HTTP alternate selection** refers to the "
"process of choosing between several alternate versions of a document for "
"a specific URL. Alternates arise because the HTTP 1.1 specification "
"allows different documents to be sent back for the same URL (depending on"
" the clients request). For example, a server might send back a GIF image "
"to a client that only accepts GIF images, and might send back a JPEG "
"image to a client that only accepts JPEG images."
msgstr ""

# e7848471607c4a9f898093405e4f8cb2
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:35
msgid ""
"The alternate selection mechanism is invoked when Traffic Server looks up"
" a URL in its cache. For each URL, Traffic Server stores a vector of "
"alternates. For each alternate in this vector, Traffic Server computes a "
"quality value between 0 and 1 that represents how \"good\" the alternate "
"is. A quality value of 0 means that the alternate is unacceptable; a "
"value of 1 means that the alternate is a perfect match."
msgstr ""

# 7211bbbeafdc4bf686703a53efe16e3a
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:42
msgid ""
"If a plugin hooks onto the ``TS_HTTP_SELECT_ALT_HOOK``, then it will be "
"called back when Traffic Server performs alternate selection. You cannot "
"register locally to the hook ``TS_HTTP_SELECT_ALT_HOOK`` by using "
"``TSHttpTxnHookAdd`` - you can only do so by using only "
"``TSHttpHookAdd``. Since Traffic Server does not actually have an HTTP "
"transaction or an HTTP session on hand when alternate selection is "
"performed, it is only valid to hook onto the global list of "
"``TS_HTTP_SELECT_ALT_HOOK``. Traffic Server calls each of the select "
"alternate hooks with the ``TS_EVENT_HTTP_SELECT_ALT`` event. The ``void "
"*edata`` argument that is passed to the continuation is a pointer to an "
"``TSHttpAltInfo`` structure. It can be used later to call the HTTP "
"alternate selection functions listed at the end of this section. Unlike "
"other hooks, this alternate selection callout is non-blocking; the "
"expectation is that the quality value for the alternate will be changed "
"by a call to ``TSHttpAltInfoQualitySet``."
msgstr ""

# 1d7ab87dabb54c32ae1a5e01610f87a9
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:60
msgid ""
"HTTP SM does not have to be reenabled using ``TSHttpTxnReenable`` or any "
"other APIs; just return from the function."
msgstr ""

# bab5a29f157144d68454732691590a09
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:63
msgid "The sample code below shows how to call the alternate APIs."
msgstr ""

# 1f029cee38044c63a4a8bbcc70d80021
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:161
msgid ""
"Traffic Server augments the alternate selection through these callouts "
"using the following algorithm:"
msgstr ""

# a1fb1fcee88b4ca3b529f21187240bbe
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:164
msgid ""
"Traffic Server computes its own quality value for the alternate, taking "
"into account the quality of the accept match, the encoding match, and the"
" language match."
msgstr ""

# ca6241c4651d403f89095c2bdebec106
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:168
msgid ""
"Traffic Server then calls out each of the continuations on the global "
"``TS_HTTP_SELECT_ALT_HOOK``'s list."
msgstr ""

# 17cd84d24e4d4f198a2183561deab924
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:171
msgid ""
"It multiplies its quality value with the value returned by each callout. "
"Since all of the values are clamped to be between 0 and 1, the final "
"value will be between 0 and 1 as well."
msgstr ""

# e033d71ae567404d9afdd5315f0500fc
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:175
msgid ""
"This algorithm also ensures that a single callout can block the usage of "
"a given alternate by specifying a quality value of 0."
msgstr ""

# aba305e5bb0f4ec3bad139e86321d3a1
#: ../../developer-guide/plugins/hooks-and-transactions/http-alternate-selection.en.rst:178
msgid ""
"A common usage for the alternate selection mechanism is when a plugin "
"transforms a document for some clients and not for others, but wants to "
"store both the transformed and unchanged document. The client's request "
"will specify whether it accepted the transformed document. The plugin "
"will then determine if the alternate matches this specification and then "
"set the appropriate quality level for the alternate."
msgstr ""

